{"bill":{"bill_id":1645698,"change_hash":"07f90f8590bc2dd5bde8b20b0a0d0641","session_id":2021,"session":{"session_id":2021,"state_id":14,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2023,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023 Regular Session","session_name":"2023 Regular Session"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/IN\/bill\/SB0078\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/iga.in.gov\/legislative\/2023\/bills\/senate\/78\/","completed":0,"status":2,"status_date":"2023-02-14","progress":[{"date":"2023-01-09","event":1},{"date":"2023-01-09","event":9},{"date":"2023-01-26","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-14","event":2}],"state":"IN","state_id":14,"bill_number":"SB0078","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"S","body_id":38,"current_body":"S","current_body_id":38,"title":"Distributions of public safety income tax revenue.","description":"Distributions of public safety income tax revenue. Requires that part of a certified distribution allocated to a county (other than Marion County), subject to a qualified township's application, be allocated among the qualified townships in the county. Provides the calculation for the amount of the allocation. Provides that a qualified township and various fire entities may apply to the county adopting body for a distribution of tax revenue. Provides that the county adopting body shall review an application and shall, before September 1 of a year, adopt a resolution requiring tax revenue to be distributed to a qualified applicant or applicants. Provides that the county adopting body shall provide a copy of the resolution to the county auditor and the department of local government finance. Provides that an adopted resolution submitted in a timely manner to the county auditor and the department of local government finance applies to distributions of tax revenue to the qualified applicant in the following calendar year and each calendar year thereafter until the qualified applicant rescinds the application. Provides that a qualified applicant that wishes to rescind its application under this subsection must notify the county adopting body in writing. Provides that if the county adopting body receives a qualified applicant's written notice to rescind its application, the county adopting body shall adopt a resolution rescinding the qualified applicant's distribution before September 1 of a year and shall provide a copy of the resolution to the county auditor and the department of local government finance.","pending_committee_id":0,"committee":[],"referrals":[{"date":"2023-01-09","committee_id":1335,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"name":"Tax and Fiscal Policy"}],"history":[{"date":"2023-01-09","action":"Authored by Senator Niemeyer","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-09","action":"First reading: referred to Committee on Tax and Fiscal Policy","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-11","action":"Senator Charbonneau added as second author","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-24","action":"Senator Dernulc added as coauthor","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-26","action":"Committee report: amend do pass, adopted","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-30","action":"Senator Bohacek added as coauthor","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-31","action":"Senator Randolph added as coauthor","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-09","action":"Amendment #4 (Niemeyer) prevailed; voice vote","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-09","action":"Second reading: amended, ordered engrossed","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-09","action":"Senator Ford Jon added as coauthor","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-13","action":"Third reading: passed; Roll Call 99: yeas 48, nays 1","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"20